race.comment: NISTIRITH (9) showed good promise in her debut campaign, just missing out on the AW at Bunbury before a spell. Her two trials coming in have been solid and she has the speed to get across from the wide alley. She looks ready to take the next step this campaign. CHASON WINS (7) is another first-up here on the back of a nice trial at Lark Hill recently. Faithfull hopping on board is a good push for her chances and she's been competitive in what look stronger maidens than this on paper. Maps beautifully and a bold showing is expected. TOMALIE (6) trialled well recently and is not to be discounted on debut. TAPITLIKEIT'SSASSY (8) has claims.
